  <static seed="1162" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalExpressionAlgebraSkills/simplifyRationalExpressions90.pg">
    <statement><p>Simplify this expression.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{2r+4x}{r^{2}+6rx+8x^{2}}}=}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{2}{r+4x}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify the expression, we first factor both the numerator and denominator, and then cross out common terms:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{2r+4x}{r^{2}+6rx+8x^{2}}} \amp = \frac{{2\mathopen{}\left(r+2x\right)}}{{\left(r+2x\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+4x\right)}} \\
                     \amp = {\frac{2}{r+4x}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
</solution>
